<headline>Severe Weather Statement issued May 05 at 1:26AM CDT until May 05 at 1:45AM CDT by NWS Tulsa</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 145 AM CDT
FOR NORTHWESTERN MADISON AND NORTHEASTERN WASHINGTON COUNTIES...
At 125 AM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 4 miles northwest of
Hindsville, moving northeast at 40 mph.
HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.
Locations in or near the path include...
Hindsville...                     Withrow Springs State Park...
Clifty...                         Forum...
Goshen...                         Rockhouse...
Alabam...                         Mayfield...
Best...
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...&lt;.75 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...60 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
